English
Following a brief affair, gym teacher Jurgen decides to marry his fellow
teacher Sibel. But that's not what their families expected: Jurgen's Flemish
parents don't understand why their only son dumped his previous girlfriend
to marry a colleague; while Sibel's Turkish brother is agitated by her
impulsive decision. Jurgen and Sibel look forward to their big day. But are
they marrying just each other, or are they marrying their families as well?
A comedy about French fries and baklava; about marriage and trust; about
Flemish modesty versus Turkish temperament.
